title: Electron fluxes ~20-4000keV and proton fluxes ~60-1500 keV from ECT/MagEIS - J. Bernard Blake (JBernard.Blake@aero.org) (The Aerospace Corporation)

info.x_cadence_note: Counts based on variable 'Epoch' in https://cdaweb.gsfc.nasa.gov/sp_phys/data/rbsp/rbspb/l3/ect/mageis/sectors/rel04/2012/rbspb_rel04_ect-mageis-l3_20120906_v8.2.0.cdf. The most common cadence occurred for 47.6948% of the 600 timesteps. Cadence = 11625 [ms] = PT11.625S.

parameters.name: FEDU_plasmagram
parameters.description: FEDU: Unidirectional Differential Electron Flux, ~20-4000 keV in 23 energy and 11 pitch angle bins (energy-angle displays). This variable is a 'virtual' variable that is computed using the function clamp_to_zero (see https://cdaweb.gsfc.nasa.gov/pub/software/cdawlib/source/virtual_funcs.pro) on the with inputs of the variables ['FEDU', 'Clamp_Threshold_Electron']. Note that some COMPONENTS may not be available from the HAPI interface. They are accessible from the raw CDF files, however.
